Always include JSP tags - Tag libraries provide custom tags that can be used to perform various tasks within JSP.

JSTL Core Tag Library: <%@ taglib uri="http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/core" prefix="c" %>
This taglib directive imports the JSTL (JavaServer Pages Standard Tag Library) core tag
library. The uri attribute specifies the Uniform Resource Identifier for the JSTL core library,
and the prefix attribute defines a prefix that will be used to reference the tags from this library in the JSP page.
In this case, the prefix is set to "c."
for example:
<c:forEach var="item" items="${itemsList}">
    <!-- JSTL core tag logic here -->
</c:forEach>


Spring Form Tag Library: <%@ taglib prefix="form" uri="http://www.springframework.org/tags/form" %>
This taglib directive imports the Spring Form tag library. The uri attribute specifies the URI for
the Spring Form tag library, and the prefix attribute defines a prefix for referencing the tags
from this library in the JSP page. In this case, the prefix is set to "form."
for example:
<form:input path="username" />
<form:select path="country" items="${countryList}" />

JSTL Functions Tag Library: <%@ taglib prefix="fn" uri="http://java.sun.com/jsp/jstl/functions" %>
This taglib directive imports the JSTL Functions tag library. The uri attribute specifies the URI
for the JSTL Functions library, and the prefix attribute defines a prefix for referencing the tags
from this library in the JSP page. In this case, the prefix is set to "fn."
for example:
${fn:length(myList)}
${fn:toUpperCase(myString)}



When using path as the input attribute the name must be the same as the one you created in your model



